---

{# ── SUMMARY · real H2 carrying the nonprofit summary prose (right after the in-brief). (H2: The short version.) ── #}
<section class="section section--compact" id="ny-ind-nonprofit-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The short version.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="stack-8">
      {%- for p in summary %}<p class="prose">{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── AI SUMMARY · five-question block. (H2: New York nonprofit accounting, in five questions.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-nonprofit-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">New York nonprofit accounting, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <dl class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled" id="ny-ind-nonprofit-ai-summary-list">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <dt class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</dt>
        <dd class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></dd>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── CHALLENGES · three places NY nonprofits lose compliance and funder trust (grid-3 buyer-cards). (H2 + 3 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-ind-nonprofit-challenges">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Why NY nonprofit books slip</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Three places New York nonprofits lose compliance and funder trust.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">A mission-focused organization can fall behind on the books that keep its status and its grants. Knowing which of these you&rsquo;re in tells us where to start.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for c in challenges %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ c.signal | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ c.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── WHAT WE HANDLE · the six services (grid-3 buyer-cards). (H2 + 6 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-nonprofit-handle">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What TechBrot handles</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">New York nonprofit accounting, done by an expert.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every engagement is scoped to your funds and programs, delivered in your own QuickBooks file by a named Certified ProAdvisor &mdash; coordinating with the independent CPA who audits and files.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in handle %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.num }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ s.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.cta | safe }}</a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── INTEGRATIONS · tools reconciled with QuickBooks (checks-list). (H2: Connected to how you run the organization.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-ind-nonprofit-integrations">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Tools we work alongside</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Connected to how you run the organization.</h2>
    </header>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      {%- for t in integrations %}<li>{{ t | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
    <p class="prose">{{ integrationsNote | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── PROCESS · four-phase engagement rhythm (grid-2 buyer-cards). (H2 + 4 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-nonprofit-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How engagements work</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From year-end scramble to filing-ready all year.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every New York nonprofit engagement follows the same four-phase rhythm &mdash; books accurate first, funder reporting second, advisory third.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for p in process %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ p.phase }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ p.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ p.body | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── ADVISORY · standing brand line carried as section prose. (H2: Clean compliance is the floor. Funding the mission is the point.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-ind-nonprofit-advisory">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Beyond the books</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Clean compliance is the floor. Funding the mission is the point.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="stack-8">
      {%- for p in advisoryBody %}<p class="prose">{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <div class="hero__actions">
      <a class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" href="/contact/?intent=new-york&amp;state=new-york&amp;source_type=industry&amp;funnel_stage=BOFU">Book the discovery call</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── FAQ · 8 verbatim contract Q/A; visible faq__list = FAQPage schema (same array). (H2: New York nonprofit accounting questions.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-nonprofit-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">New York nonprofit accounting questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="ny-ind-nonprofit-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="ny-ind-nonprofit-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── EXPERT REVIEW · firm-level, no founder name (byline-block + meta-reviewed). (H2: Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-ind-nonprofit-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="byline-block">
      <div class="byline-block__mark" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div>
        <p class="byline-block__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline-block__review">TechBrot Inc. &middot; Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>This page reflects how TechBrot handles New York nonprofit engagements. It is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at <strong>TechBrot Inc.</strong>, a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm, and reviewed for technical accuracy on fund accounting (restricted vs. unrestricted net assets), functional-expense allocation, grant revenue recognition, and the <a href="https://www.charitiesnys.com/" rel="noopener nofollow">CHAR500</a> annual filing to the NY Attorney General&rsquo;s Charities Bureau and <a href="https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-990" rel="noopener nofollow">IRS Form 990</a>. TechBrot maintains the CHAR500-ready workpapers and coordinates with your independent CPA, who performs any required audit or review and files. Confirm your filing tier with the Charities Bureau or your CPA.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for c in reviewCreds %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ c.label }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ c.detail | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-07</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-07</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-07 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── RELATED · NY services & industries (grid-2 buyer-cards). (H2 + 4 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-nonprofit-related">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Related New York services &amp; industries.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for r in related %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ r.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ r.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ r.href }}">{{ r.cta | safe }}</a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
